{"steps": [{"title": "Photosynthesis Stages", "image_show_confidencescore": 0.0, "lang": "en-US", "frames": [{"frame_type": "concept", "text": "The two main stages of photosynthesis are:\n1. Light-dependent reactions\n2. Calvin cycle (light-independent reactions)", "highlight": ["Light-dependent reactions", "Calvin cycle"], "speech": "Photosynthesis happens in two main stages: the light-dependent reactions and the Calvin cycle.", "tts_engine": "android", "voice_role": "teacher", "duration_ms": 4000, "quiz_answer": "", "quiz_options": [], "quiz_correct_index": -1, "quiz_model_answer": "", "quiz_keywords": [], "fill_blanks": [], "quiz_correct_order": [], "diagram_type": "", "data": {}, "svg_elements": []}, {"frame_type": "diagram", "text": "Visualizing the flow of photosynthesis.", "highlight": ["Light-dependent reactions", "Calvin cycle"], "speech": "In the light-dependent reactions, chlorophyll captures light energy to split water, releasing oxygen and creating energy carriers. The Calvin cycle then uses these energy carriers to convert carbon dioxide into glucose, the plant's food.", "tts_engine": "gemini", "voice_role": "teacher", "duration_ms": 5000, "quiz_answer": "", "quiz_options": [], "quiz_correct_index": -1, "quiz_model_answer": "", "quiz_keywords": [], "fill_blanks": [], "quiz_correct_order": [], "svg_html": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n<meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width,initial-scale=1,user-scalable=no\">\n<style>\n  *{margin:0;padding:0;box-sizing:border-box}\n  html,body{\n    width:100%;height:100vh;\n    background:#1A2B1A;\n    display:flex;flex-direction:column;\n    align-items:center;justify-content:center;\n    overflow:hidden;\n  }\n  svg{width:100%;max-width:100%;flex:1;min-height:0}\n  #controls{\n    display:flex;gap:8px;justify-content:center;padding:4px 0;flex-shrink:0;\n  }\n  button{\n    background:#2a3f2a;border:1px solid #4a6a4a;color:#e0f0e0;\n    border-radius:6px;padding:4px 14px;font-size:14px;cursor:pointer;\n  }\n</style>\n</head>\n<body>\n<svg id=\"diagram\" viewBox=\"0 0 400 300\" width=\"100%\"\n     xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" style=\"display:block\">\n</svg>\n<div id=\"controls\"></div>\n<script src=\"diagram_engine.js\"></script>\n<script>\n(function() {\n  var svg        = document.getElementById('diagram');\n  var descriptor = {\"title\": \"Photosynthesis Stages\", \"steps\": [\"Light energy captured\", \"Water splits, O2\", \"Energy carriers made\", \"CO2 enters cycle\", \"Sugar (glucose) formed\"]};\n  var engine     = new DiagramEngine(svg, descriptor, { phaseMs: 2500 });\n  try {\n    Diagrams.flowArrow(engine, svg, descriptor);\n  } catch(e) {\n    var t = document.createElementNS('http://www.w3.org/2000/svg','text');\n    t.setAttribute('x','200'); t.setAttribute('y','150');\n    t.setAttribute('text-anchor','middle'); t.setAttribute('fill','#FF6B6B');\n    t.setAttribute('font-size','12');\n    t.textContent = 'flowArrow: ' + e.message;\n    svg.appendChild(t);\n  }\n  createControls(engine, document.getElementById('controls'));\n  engine.start();\n})();\n</script>\n</body>\n</html>\n"}, {"frame_type": "concept", "text": "Chlorophyll is the key pigment that absorbs sunlight for photosynthesis.\nIt's what makes plants green!", "highlight": ["Chlorophyll"], "speech": "Chlorophyll is the vital green pigment in plant cells that captures light energy. Think of it as the solar panel of the plant!", "tts_engine": "gemini", "voice_role": "teacher", "duration_ms": 4000, "quiz_answer": "", "quiz_options": [], "quiz_correct_index": -1, "quiz_model_answer": "", "quiz_keywords": [], "fill_blanks": [], "quiz_correct_order": [], "diagram_type": "", "data": {}, "svg_elements": []}]}, {"title": "Quiz & Summary", "image_show_confidencescore": 0.0, "image_description": null, "lang": "en-US", "frames": [{"frame_type": "quiz_mcq", "text": "Which part of photosynthesis uses sunlight to create energy carriers?", "highlight": ["sunlight", "energy carriers"], "speech": "Which part of photosynthesis uses sunlight to create energy carriers?", "tts_engine": "android", "voice_role": "quiz", "duration_ms": 4000, "quiz_answer": "Light-dependent reactions", "quiz_options": ["Calvin cycle", "Chlorophyll absorption", "Light-dependent reactions", "Glucose synthesis"], "quiz_correct_index": 2, "quiz_model_answer": "", "quiz_keywords": [], "fill_blanks": [], "quiz_correct_order": [], "diagram_type": "", "data": {}, "svg_elements": []}, {"frame_type": "summary", "text": "Photosynthesis involves light-dependent reactions and the Calvin cycle.\nChlorophyll captures sunlight to produce energy carriers, which then help create glucose from CO\u2082.", "highlight": ["light-dependent reactions", "Calvin cycle", "Chlorophyll", "glucose"], "speech": "To recap, photosynthesis is a two-stage process. First, the light-dependent reactions use chlorophyll and sunlight to create energy carriers and release oxygen. Then, the Calvin cycle uses these carriers to convert carbon dioxide into glucose, the food that fuels plant growth.", "tts_engine": "google", "voice_role": "assistant", "duration_ms": 6000, "quiz_answer": "", "quiz_options": [], "quiz_correct_index": -1, "quiz_model_answer": "", "quiz_keywords": [], "fill_blanks": [], "quiz_correct_order": [], "diagram_type": "", "data": {}, "svg_elements": []}]}]}